If you want a **minimal NGINX setup on Manjaro** (clean, no clutter, perfect for learning/reverse proxy), do this

---

# 1. Install only NGINX

sudo pacman -S nginx

That’s it — no extra packages needed.

---

# 2. Clean default config (make it minimal)

Edit:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/nginx.conf

Replace EVERYTHING with this minimal config:

events {}

http {
    server {
        listen 80;

        location /api {
            proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
        }
    }
}

---

# ▶️ 3. Start NGINX

sudo systemctl start nginx

Enable on boot:
sudo systemctl enable nginx

---

# 4. Test config
sudo nginx -t
---

# 5. Test proxy

curl "http://localhost/api?key=test"

---

# What this minimal setup includes

✔ No static files
✔ No MIME types
✔ No logging config
✔ Only reverse proxy

Pure backend proxy 

---

# Even more minimal (extreme)

events {}

http {
    server {
        listen 80;
        location / {
            proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8080;
        }
    }
}

---

# Key idea

In **NGINX**:

* Everything is optional except:

  * `events {}`
  * `http {}`
  * `server {}`
  * `location {}`

---

# For YOU (best setup)

Since you’re building backend systems:

* Keep NGINX minimal
* Add features only when needed:

  * logging
  * SSL
  * load balancing

